Class FieldInfoScreen
    Initialize state with:
        - Field details
        - Field's temperature data

    Function build (Building the UI)
        Display app bar with the title "Field Information"
        
        Retrieve and display field details:
            - Field name
            - Field location (latitude, longitude)
            - Field size
            - Field's crop type

        Display a section for "Temperature Data"
        Retrieve and display the field's temperature data for the current month
        Display average temperature for the current month

        IF user clicks on "Back" THEN
            Navigate back to the FieldListScreen
        ENDIF
End Class

1. Start
2. Display app bar with title "Field Information"
3. Retrieve and display the field's details:
   a. Field name
   b. Field location
   c. Field size
   d. Crop type
4. Display a "Temperature Data" section
5. Retrieve and display the field's temperature data for the current month
6. Display average temperature for the month
7. User can click "Back" to navigate to the FieldListScreen
8. End

1. Entities: 
   - User
2. Processes: 
   - Retrieve and display field details
   - Retrieve and display field's temperature data
   - Handle user interactions (navigating back)
3. Data Stores: 
   - Firebase Firestore (for field details and temperature data)
4. Data Flow:
   - System retrieves the field details and temperature data from Firebase Firestore
   - System displays the retrieved details and data to the user
   - User interacts (navigates back)
   - System navigates back to FieldListScreen based on user's action
